articles.description: We stacked the top recruiting classes in the country as schools make their final moves.
articles.headline: 2024 college football recruiting class rankings: Top 75 schools

images.name: Miami Hurricanes head coach Mario Cristobal gestures in the second half against the Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Hard Rock Stadium.  [608x342]
images.alt: Miami Hurricanes head coach Mario Cristobal gestures in the second half against the Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Hard Rock Stadium.
images.credit: Photo by Jasen Vinlove/USA TODAY Sports

images.name: James Franklin [608x342] - Copy
images.alt: Penn State coach James Franklin, wearing a white hoodie, celebrates after winning the Rose Bowl.
images.caption: James Franklin and the Nittany Lions have 10 ESPN 300 commitments, rising into the top five of the 2024 recruiting class rankings.

images.name: Billy Napier [608x342]
images.alt: Florida football coach Billy Napier points as he walks onto the field.
images.caption: Coach Billy Napier has landed four ESPN 300 commitments over the past week as Florida skyrocketed from No. 11 to No. 4 in the 2024 recruiting class rankings.

images.name: Dabo Swinney [608x342]
images.alt: Clemson football coach Dabo Swinney locks arms with his players before a game.
images.caption: Clemson coach Dabo Swinney added three ESPN 300 commitments over the past month as the Tigers climbed into the top 10 of the 2024 recruiting class rankings.

images.name: Shane Beamer [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: South Carolina hasn't finished with a top-10 recruiting class in over 15 years, but Shane Beamer is looking to change that.

images.name: Kirby Smart [608x342]
images.caption: Kirby Smart and Georgia have finished with a top-three recruiting class each of the past seven cycles, and the Bulldogs are seeking to make it eight.

images.name: Ryan Day and Jim Harbaugh [608x342] - Copy (2)
images.caption: Ohio State and Michigan are not only competing on the field, but are battling inside the top three on the recruiting trail for 2024.

images.name: Kirby Smart [608x342]
images.alt: Georgia coach Kirby Smart raises his arms in celebration after winning the national championship game.

images.name: Marcus Freeman [608x342]
images.alt: Notre Dame coach Marcus Freeman celebrates on the sideline.
images.caption: Marcus Freeman and Notre Dame start the 2024 recruiting cycle with the second-ranked class.

images.name: Shane Beamer [608x342]
images.alt: South Carolina coach Shane Beamer celebrates after a win over Clemson.
images.caption: After finishing outside of the top 75 in 2021, Shane Beamer has led South Carolina to top-20 finishes in the recruiting class rankings for the 2022 and 2023 cycles and has the Gamecocks inside the top 10 to start the 2024 cycle.
